CAPE TOWN - A 28-year-old accused of being a drug mule is expected to appear in the Bellville Magistrate's Court on Thursday after she was caught at Cape Town International Airport for being in possession of cocaine and heroin worth a combined street value of R870 000. The suspect was intercepted by an integrated multidisciplinary operation that included the Hawks’ South African Narcotics Enforcement Bureau together with Crime Intelligence and Customs division from Sars). The joint team acted on a tip-off about a suspect travelling from Sao Paulo, Brazil to Cape Town, via Qatar Airways. Upon searching her luggage, the authorities allegedly found more than 2.7kg of cocaine and 200g of heroin concealed in her luggage and shoes. She was immediately placed under arrest and the drugs seized for further investigation. The acting provincial head of the Hawks in the Western Cape Brigadier Mushavhaduvha Ramovha praised the joint team for the drug bust. “This is an indication of the capacity and capabilities of the joint security forces to decisively deal with the numerous attempts to use the airport as a thoroughfare for drug smuggling.” Meanwhile the SAPS Maitland Flying Squad responded to information relating to drugs at an identified address in Gugulethu on Tuesday and upon arrival they searched the address and found mandrax tablets to the value of R138 500. A 50-year-old man was arrested and detained on a charge of possession of drugs. Once charged he will appear in the Athlone Magistrate’s Court. Cape Times